            <div class="lesson-content">
                <h1>Module 1: Foundations of Financial Markets</h1>
                <p><strong>üéØ GOAL:</strong> Understand what markets are and why they exist</p>

                <div class="lesson-section">
                    <h2>1.1 What Are Financial Markets?</h2>
                    
                    <div class="key-concept">
                        <h3>üìñ Definition</h3>
                        <p><strong>Financial markets</strong> are platforms where buyers and sellers trade financial instruments like stocks, bonds, currencies, and derivatives.</p>
                    </div>

                    <h3>The Marketplace Analogy</h3>
                    <p>Think of financial markets as a giant global marketplace where instead of buying apples or cars, people trade:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Currencies</strong> (US Dollars for Euros)</li>
                        <li><strong>Ownership</strong> (Shares of companies)</li>
                        <li><strong>Debt</strong> (Bonds - loans to governments or companies)</li>
                        <li><strong>Commodities</strong> (Gold, oil, wheat)</li>
                    </ul>

                    <div class="key-concept">
                        <h3>üí° Key Insight</h3>
                        <p>Markets exist to facilitate <strong>price discovery</strong> - determining the fair value of assets through supply and demand.</p>
                    </div>

                    <h3>Market Functions</h3>
                    <div class="grid grid-2">
                        <div class="card">
                            <h4>Capital Formation</h4>
                            <p>Companies raise money by selling shares to investors</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card">
                            <h4>Risk Transfer</h4>
                            <p>Investors can hedge risks using derivatives and other instruments</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card">
                            <h4>Liquidity Provision</h4>
                            <p>Markets allow quick buying and selling of assets</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card">
                            <h4>Price Discovery</h4>
                            <p>Collective wisdom determines asset prices</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="interactive-exercise">
                    <h3>üß† Knowledge Check</h3>
                    <p><strong>Question:</strong> What is the primary purpose of financial markets?</p>
                    <div style="display: flex; gap: var(--space-md); justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; margin: var(--space-md) 0;">
                        <button class="btn btn-outline" onclick="checkAnswer(1)">A) Make people rich quickly</button>
                        <button class="btn btn-outline" onclick="checkAnswer(2)">B) Facilitate trading and price discovery</button>
                        <button class="btn btn-outline" onclick="checkAnswer(3)">C) Create complex financial products</button>
                    </div>
                    <div id="answer-result" style="margin-top: var(--space-md); font-weight: bold;"></div>
                </div>

                <div class="lesson-section">
                    <h2>1.2 Why Markets Exist</h2>
                    
                    <h3>Three Primary Reasons</h3>
                    <div class="grid grid-3">
                        <div class="card">
                            <h4>üí∞ Capital Allocation</h4>
                            <p>Money flows to where it's most productive. Growing companies get funding, investors get returns.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card">
                            <h4>üõ°Ô∏è Risk Management</h4>
                            <p>Businesses and investors can protect against adverse price movements.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card">
                            <h4>üìà Speculation</h4>
                            <p>Traders attempt to profit from price changes, providing liquidity to markets.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="key-concept">
                        <h3>üåç Global Economic Engine</h3>
                        <p>Without financial markets, economic growth would slow dramatically. Companies couldn't raise capital efficiently, and international trade would be much more difficult.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

